                           <q>Notes marked "Ǧ", "ŠR", "Anwār", "Muġnī", "Maḥallī", "ǦǦ", "Imdād", "Ǧamal", "Šarqāwī", "Ibn Ḥaǧar", "Buǧayrimī", "Baǧūr", "Taǧrīd"</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r-2v">-2r-2v</locus>
                           <desc>Loose folio</desc>
                           <q/>
                           <note>Three loose fragments with some text. The largest piece contains a fragment of a devotional text. The second is a small slip of white paper with handwritten text on one side, only few words remain. The  third one is a small fragment of a printed book page.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#ir">-ir</locus>
                           <desc>Loose folio</desc>
                           <q/>
                           <note>Badly damaged fragment of a folio. Only very little of the text readable but it appears to be a devotional poem.</note>
